title: Frank Lloyd Wright Saguaro Puzzle
description:
Act like an architect and piece together a Frank Lloyd Wright® (American, 1867–1959) favorite. Sort through 1,054 gold foil-stamped puzzle pieces to engineer Saguaro Forms and Cactus Flowers, a design Wright created for an unpublished Liberty Magazine cover in 1927. Made with 90% recycled paper and printed with non-toxic ink.

8 ¼ x 11 ¼ x 2 in.
